Additional fix for SDK-25312  which caused a regression SDK-29306. If a Skin class didn't already have something declared that would require a [Bindable] implementation, the generated hostComponent property (also [Bindable]) wouldn't dispatch change events.
The problem was that the BindableExtension parse1 wouldn't set it's first pass generator in the compilation unit context so HostComponentExtension wouldn't find it in parse2.

QE notes: Please ensure we have a Skin class that doesn't include a declaration with an id attribute or anything else that would cause the class to use [Bindable] and then test a binding statement to the hostComponent variable (which is generated due to [HostComponent] metadata).
